# Generated API contract. The SDK drift gate compares the committed file byte
# for byte against a freshly generated one, and the generator emits LF. Without
# this rule a Windows checkout (core.autocrlf=true) rewrites it to CRLF, so the
# gate reports permanent drift that regenerating cannot fix — the commit would
# just be converted back. Pin it to LF on every platform.
sdk/openapi.json text eol=lf
